         I agree. My question is "why now? why this zone?". Look around since Kunark...Spirocs, Raptors, Ulthorks, Giants, Wurms...you name it. In almost every zone in Kunark+ you can find someone quadding. I never saw them put traps and horribly resistant high HP mobs in these zones to stop it from happening. Why wait for 3 expansions and THEN nerf a zone where a Necro could actually sit back and enjoy themselves? Or did I just answer my own question there? Necro...enjoying themselves...must pay?? Hmmmm...</P><P>Just stupid to put so much crap in a zone where we could actually just leave the rest of the game behind and kick back and have FUN. Look at Seb and Chardok, and to some extent Cazic Thule now. AE groups OWN 5,6,7 spawn points at a time...and you want to pick The Grey out and nerf it to hell sideways. It makes no sense. I can understand if there were too many people quadding or AEing in this zone...maybe you could have sat down and thought up something a little more creative to solve the problem though. Rather than putting these damn half zonewide aggro stonegrabbers and worm traps every two feet...maybe you should have worked on resists, or buff the mobs damage up or immunity to stun or some such. Just silly to kill such a cool zone like that.</P><P><img src="http://www.netset.com/~blazer/sig00b.jpg" border=0></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
